==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/Ààl…ô ät É/}}
* {{rhymes|en|…ô ät É}}

===Etymology 1===
{{wikipedia|Loach (fish)}}
[[Image:Misgurnus anguillicaudatus.jpg|thumb|200px|''[[Misgurnus anguillicaudatus]]'', the {{vern|muddy loach}}]]
{{wikispecies|Cobitidae}}
From {{inh|en|enm|loche}}, from {{der|en|fro|loche}}, further origin {{unk|en|title=uncertain}}, possibly from {{der|en|VL.|*laukka||loach}}, which could be from {{der|en|cel-gau|*leuca||loach, slug}}, also attested as the feminine name {{m|cel-gau|Leuca}}, from {{m|cel-gau|leux||bright, light}}, a reference to  slugs' bright appearance, the fish later being associated due to similarities to the slug.<ref>{{R:American_Heritage_Dictionary|loach}}</ref>

====Noun====
{{en-noun|es}}

# A bottom-feeding freshwater fish in the superfamily or suborder [[Cobitoidea]].
## Any {{vern|true loach}}, of the family [[Cobitidae]].
## A similar fish in one of three other families of [[Cypriniformes]]: {{taxlink|Botiidae|family}}, [[Balitoridae]], and {{taxlink|Gyrinocheilidae|family}}.

=====Derived terms=====
* {{vern|clown loach}} ({{taxlink|Chromobotia macracanthus|species|ver=171212}})
* {{l|en|dojo loach}} (''[[Misgurnus anguillicaudatus]]'')
* {{l|en|hillstream loach}} ([[Balitoridae]])
* {{vern|muddy loach}} (''[[Misgurnus anguillicaudatus]]'')
* {{vern|oriental loach}} (''[[Misgurnus anguillicaudatus]]'')
* {{vern|panda loach}} ({{taxlink|Yaoshania pachychilus|species|ver=171212}})
* [[pond loach]] (''[[Misgurnus anguillicaudatus]]'')
* {{vern|river loach}} ([[Balitoridae]])
* [[spined loach]] (''{{ll|mul|Cobitis taenia}}'')
* {{vern|sucking loach}} ({{taxlink|Gyrinocheilus|genus|ver=171212}} spp.)
* {{l|en|weather loach}} (''[[Misgurnus]]'' spp.)

